<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,617,1074]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,501,761,786]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[510,758,761,786]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Colobosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[510,758,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Colobosaura modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the Brazilian Cerrado, reaching moreover some forested areas outside this region (
<figureCitation box="[606,690,797,822]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1571,1593]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,313,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1549]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Distribution of examined material of Cercosaura sp. 1, Colobosaura modesta, and Gymnophthalmus underwoodi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581985/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). It also occurs in a small portion of Cerrado that enters 
<collectingCountry box="[1332,1436,798,822]" name="Paraguay" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<collectingRegion box="[1332,1436,798,822]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Paraguay</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
(Motte 
<emphasis box="[234,291,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2009). In 
<collectingCountry box="[408,477,833,858]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Brasil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[823,876,834,858]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[887,998,833,858]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1010,1127,833,858]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1138,1198,833,858]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Piauí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1278,834,858]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1289,1432,833,858]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,219,869,894]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[237,391,870,894]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[408,654,869,894]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[672,740,869,894]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[758,917,869,894]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[934,1057,869,894]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, and in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1397,869,894]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Distrito Federal</collectingRegion>
. In 
<taxonomicName box="[151,266,905,930]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="17" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
it is known from southern and eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[736,786,906,930]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Pará</collectingRegion>
state, in 
<collectingCountry box="[899,971,905,930]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[986,1236,905,930]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Colobosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[986,1236,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Colobosaura modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits cerrado sensu strictu, dense cerrado, wet grasslands, gallery forest within the Cerrado (Nogueira 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2005; Recoder &amp; Nogueira 2007; Vaz-Silva 
<emphasis box="[691,748,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2007; Recoder 
<emphasis box="[928,985,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2011; Morais 
<emphasis box="[1151,1208,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2012), dry forest of Caatinga (Borges-Nojosa &amp; Gascon 2005; Freire 
<emphasis box="[701,757,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2012), primary and secondary terra firme and varzea forests, and enclaves of saxicolous vegetation (campo rupestre) in 
<taxonomicName box="[807,922,1049,1074]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="17" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazônia</taxonomicName>
(Nascimento 
<emphasis box="[1079,1135,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
1987; Ávila-Pires 1995).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
